        " سَفَرٍ أَوْ حَضَرٍ فَقَالَ «لاَ بَأْسَ بِهِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1047 - Sahl ibn al-Yas'a asked Abu Al-Hasan al-Awwal (as) about a man who prays a voluntary prayer sitting while he does not have any illness, whether in travel or while at home.\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm in that”."
        ]
      }
